headline: TMO Q4 Deep Dive: Product Innovation and Strategic Acquisitions Drive Mixed Market Reaction
summary: Life sciences company Thermo Fisher (NYSE:TMO) reported revenue ahead of Wall Streets expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 7.2% year on year to $12.22 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $6.57 per share was 1.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
